name: rails8
description: Ruby on Rails 8 project with Ruby 3.4.1
glob: app/**/*.{rb,erb}

---
When working with this Rails 8 project, follow these guidelines:

1. Ruby Version
- Use Ruby 3.4.1 features and syntax
- Use pattern matching where appropriate
- Use endless methods for single-line methods
- Use numbered parameters for simple blocks

2. Modern Rails Practices
- Use Propshaft for asset pipeline
- Use Import Maps for JavaScript management
- Use Turbo and Stimulus for frontend interactions
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Use SolidQueue for background jobs
- Use SolidCache for caching
- Use SolidCable for Action Cable

3. Testing
- Use system tests with Capybara for integration testing
- Use FactoryBot instead of fixtures
- Follow Rails testing best practices
- Test Turbo and Stimulus interactions in system tests

4. Security
- Use Rails security best practices
- Never commit sensitive data
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Follow OWASP guidelines 